CommentBlocks.Comment:
bit 3 = 1 means SHIFT pressed
bit 4 = 0 means CAPS LOCK engaged
bit 5 = 0 means SHIFT LOCK engaged
bit 6 = 1 means CTRL pressed
bit 7 = 1 means SHIFT enabled

ROM type byte:
b7 = ROM contains a service entry
b6 = ROM contains a language entry
b5 = ROM contains Tube transfer address and any other addresses after the copyright string
b4 = ROM contains Electron key expansions
b3-b0 = ROM CPU type:
0 6502 BASIC           8 Z80
 1 Turbo6502            9 32016
 2 6502                10 -
 3 68000               11 80186
 4 -                   12 80286
 5 -                   13 ARM
 6 -                   14 -
 7 PDP-11              15 -

DataInfo.Comment: 0 - soft reset (Break), 1 - Power On, 2 - Hard Reset (Ctrl-Break)
